This function intercepts a model definition right after it is created. It iterates through all locally defined fields on that model, specifically checking for the presence of HStoreField types.

```python
def create_model(self, model):
        """Ran when a new model is created."""

        for field in model._meta.local_fields:
            if not isinstance(field, HStoreField):
                continue

            self.add_field(model, field)
```

Successfully identifying and filtering for `HStoreField` ensures they are correctly processed by `self.add_field` during the initial setup phase of the model.
